Step 1 — Navigate to Volumes:
        Go to AWS Console → EC2
        In the left panel, under Elastic Block Store → Click "Volumes"
        Click "Create Volume"
Step 2 — Configure the Volume:
      Under Volume Type → Select gp2(General Purpose SSD)
      Under Size → Enter 2 GB
      Under Availability Zone → Select the same Availability Zone as your EC2 instance
      ⚠️ (This is important — EBS volumes can only attach to EC2 instances in the same Availability Zone)
      Click "Create Volume"
Step 3 — Attach the Volume to EC2:
        Once the volume is created, select the newly created volume
        Click Actions → "Attach Volume"
        In the Instance dropdown → Select your EC2 Instance
        Click "Attach Volume"
Step 4 — Verify the Attached Volume:
        Go to EC2 → Instances
        Select your EC2 Instance
        Click the "Storage" tab at the bottom
        Under Block Devices → You will now see 2 volumes:
